description.p:
By means of molecular markers capable of differentiating between the different accessions of which each DH was composed, the genomic constitution of each of the DHs was examined, in order to identify the origin of each of the five chromosomes in every individual DH plant. Two DH plants were selected in this manner:
A first plant harbouring chromosome I of Cvi in combination with the remaining 4 chromosomes from Col-0;
A second plant harbouring chromosome I of Cvi in combination with the remaining 4 chromosomes from Ler.

In the current example this problem is overcome, by including additional experimental steps in the procedure, after selection of the following two DH plants:
A first plant harbouring chromosome I of Cvi in combination with the remaining 4 chromosomes from Col-0;
A second plant harbouring chromosome I of Cvi in combination with the remaining 4 chromosomes from Ler.
